<subSubSection id="6A76983FD9356D7A3D4828F606307EA9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="396A03B695D9B99DCEF47DA9DC0114E2" pageNumber="1">Introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A52E099D65D102EC9171926CE636098B" pageNumber="1">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="2B8BCFD24D1BF71D898BA41A16EA008B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops Gill</taxonomicName>
are small to moderate size (largest with about 180 mm SL), occurring in South America throughout the Orinoco, Amazonas, Essequibo, Corantijn, and Approuague drainages. The genus, proposed for 
<taxonomicName id="4E0C345A570FAA54BD4C3818DD7A9E3C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7CE765F5-571B-4CA9-9C77-29A55E3509C6" authority="Cuvier, 1830" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1830" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Micropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Micropogon trifilis Müller &amp; Troschel 1849:622" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trifilis">
Micropogon trifilis 
<normalizedToken id="FEC4F08C1C58765B0A0152E7207315A1" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
and Troschel (1848)
</taxonomicName>
, was described based on material that originated in Guyana, and was first characterized by having three barbels, small pores on the chin, and a small, inferior, horizontal mouth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FEE23441040A5D13D29DB129C105EC4D" pageNumber="2">
Jordan and Eigenmann (1889), Campos (1942), Fowler (1954), and Chao (1978) studied aspects of the taxonomy of the genus, and of these studies, the first is the most complete in terms of geographic coverage, type-specimen examination, and diagnosis, but does not allow the recognition of all of the valid species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C169DEE2CC62315436C88173519C902" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
. In order to resolve this problem, this paper provides a complete taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName id="F9D3B4B52AF2978A2817926D04F561FD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A1A52A20-86AC-4DC1-89BB-A5D1CC1CBBDB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Pachypops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypops Gill 1861:87" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypops</taxonomicName>
, including the redescriptions of all recognized species and the description of a new species.
</paragraph>
